President Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver his Freedom Day address to South Africa. Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver his Freedom Day address to South Africa. The theme for this year’s Freedom Day is "solidarity and the triumph of the human spirit in challenging times”. READ: Cuban health professionals arrive in SA The president welcomed a team of over 200 medical professionals to South Africa. They're in the country to support efforts in the fight against the spread of COVID-19.